artments ranging from  to more than  square feet that will rent from  to  per month the acre project site is vacant land there will be onsite parking a fitness center rooftop gardens a business center a swimming pool and aroundtheclock security according to a news release some units will have private balconies or terraces and fireplaces project funding comes from a us department of housing and urban development mortgage state equity and brownfield tax credits among other sources detroitbased sachse construction is the general contractor on the project birminghambased mcintosh poris associates is the project architect related linkswayne state medical office building among  projects receiving up to m in tax incentiveseast jefferson corridor draws investors despite challengessearchable database real estate deals in metro detroitcampus martius picnic table was scene of landmark detroit building sale deal michigan morning newsletterget a roundup of important news that happens each day facebook twitter linkedin news this weeks issuebreaking newsdetroitmichigan newsartsentertainmentauto suppliersmanufacturingentrepreneurshipfooddrinkhealth carejobstalentnonprofitspeopleelectionsreal estatesports businesstechnology blogs  opinion keith crainron fourniermary kramerother voiceseditorials extras all extrasyear in review things to do this weekendauto showdetroit homecomingflint water crisisfood economygiving guidemackinac policy conferencemichigan stock centermichigan womens directorymost connectedwayne county jail data data centerbook of listsdirectory creative detroit awards all awardsnominate in their s under  names to know in it names to know in real estatebest managed nonprofitsbiggest dealscool places to workeureka index mostinnovative companiesfast  fastestgrowing companieshealth care heroesmichigan change makersmost influential womennewsmaker of the year events all eventscrains eventslocal eventssponsored eventssubmit your event multimedia multimediavideophoto galleries