 the lafateyye foods grocery store will be replaced by a threebuilding apartment complex that will be built by local developer walter cohen through his development company ducharme place llc under plans designed by mcintosh poris associates model d reports that construction at the longstalled ducharme place will start this fall scheduled for completion in late  ducharme place will have  marketrate apartments in a mix of studios onebedroom and twobedroom units the contemporary amenities ducharme place – lafayette park include a common courtyard and pool green roof and ground level parking with nearly  spaces according to the news source the parking spaces will be incorporated underneath three platforms that will raise one story above the ground to support the residential buildings according to mlivecom the cost per unit hasn’t been determined yet but the development team estimates that it will be slightly less than other residential units located in the downtown and midtown areas estimated to cost around  million the ducharme place project is partly financed under the hud  d program that allows up to year mortgage loans to encourage the new construction or substantial rehabilitation of multifamily rental or coop housing for moderateincome families elderly and the handicapped earlier this month the residential project received  million in tax incentives from the detroit brownfield redevelopment authority model d reported   click here for more market data on detroit   renderings via mcintosh poris associates     related posts flexngate adds office space near detroit  july   california investor acquires michigan office property  july   madison realty capital sells richmond plaza  july   friedman secures buyer for detroit office building  july   detroit’s orchestra place changes hands  july   top stories skyview facilitates sale of va self storage facility  july   panoche valley solar project to be downsized  july   first cpace deal closes in washington dc  july   brazil